# BooksForge — example environment.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (which is gitignored) when you need any of
# the variables below set.  None of them are REQUIRED at runtime — the
# desktop app reads its configuration from `~/.booksforge/settings.toml`
# and from the project bundle's `manifest.toml`.  These are dev-loop
# convenience variables only.
#
# Refs: outputs/TOOLCHAIN.md, outputs/SECURITY_PRIVACY.md.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# sqlx compile-time query verification
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# All sqlx queries (`query!` / `query_as!` macros) are checked at compile
# time.  The repository commits a `.sqlx/` offline cache, so a fresh
# clone builds with `SQLX_OFFLINE=true` (the default for `cargo build`
# in CI).  If you ADD or CHANGE a query, you have two options:
#
# A) Set DATABASE_URL to a local SQLite file and run `cargo sqlx prepare`
#    to regenerate the cache, then commit the updated `.sqlx/` files.
# B) Set SQLX_OFFLINE=true and ensure your query matches an existing
#    cached query.

# DATABASE_URL=sqlite://./booksforge-dev.db
# SQLX_OFFLINE=true

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Logging — Rust `tracing` envelope
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# At runtime the desktop app writes rotating logs to
# ~/.booksforge/logs/.  These env vars only affect dev-loop terminals
# where you `cargo run` or `cargo test`.

# RUST_LOG=info,booksforge_orchestrator=debug,booksforge_ollama=debug
# RUST_BACKTRACE=1

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Ollama
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# At runtime the host comes from `~/.booksforge/settings.toml` (default:
# http://127.0.0.1:11434, the loopback default).  The env var below is
# ONLY honoured by some integration tests; the production build always
# reads the settings file.  Setting this to a non-loopback host will
# fail the privacy-invariants test suite — see
# crates/booksforge-orchestrator/tests/privacy_invariants.rs.

# OLLAMA_HOST=http://127.0.0.1:11434

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Tauri build hints (Vite reads these)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# When running `cargo tauri dev`, Tauri sets these for you.  Override
# only if you know what you are doing.

# TAURI_ENV_DEBUG=true     # generates source maps in the Vite build

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Release-pipeline secrets (CI ONLY — never set locally)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# These are listed in `.github/workflows/release.yml` and stored in
# GitHub Secrets.  They are NEVER read locally and should not appear
# in your `.env`.  Listed here for awareness only.
#
# - APPLE_DEVELOPER_ID_CERT
# - APPLE_DEVELOPER_ID_PASSWORD
# - APPLE_NOTARIZATION_APPLE_ID
# - APPLE_NOTARIZATION_TEAM_ID
# - APPLE_NOTARIZATION_PASSWORD
# - WINDOWS_SIGNING_CERT
# - WINDOWS_SIGNING_PASSWORD
# - TAURI_SIGNING_PRIVATE_KEY
# - TAURI_SIGNING_PRIVATE_KEY_PASSWORD
